import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day_of_week'] = pd.Categorical(data['day_of_week'], categories=['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday', 'Sunday'], ordered=True)
    sns.barplot(x='day_of_week', y='count', data=data, ci=None, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Day of the Week')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the average count per day of the week?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['time'] = data['time'].dt.time
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['count'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
